From e5ed6cee58afb13d33525f248e287e3b9feec824 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: gahingwoo <huhuvmb88@outlook.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Jun 2026 16:23:19 +1200
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] iommu/rockchip: clear stale page fault before enabling
 stall

A Rockchip IOMMU bank that has PAGE_FAULT_ACTIVE set will silently
reject CMD_ENABLE_STALL, causing rk_iommu_enable_stall() to time out
even though the bus is otherwise idle.  This can happen when firmware
leaves the IOMMU with a latched fault from an unmapped access that
occurred before the DTE was programmed (e.g. during NPU power-on).

Before issuing CMD_ENABLE_STALL, check each bank for the combination
of PAGE_FAULT_ACTIVE and IDLE (no transaction in flight).  If both are
set, clear the latched fault with CMD_ZAP_CACHE + CMD_PAGE_FAULT_DONE,
the same sequence used in the IRQ handler.  This is safe because IDLE
guarantees no active transaction will be disrupted.

Observed on RK3576 (Radxa ROCK 4D): the first two or three attach calls
to the NPU IOMMU produced spurious "Enable stall request timed out,
status: 0x00000b / 0x00001d" messages until the stale boot-time fault
was cleared by an interrupt.  With this fix those messages disappear.
---
 drivers/iommu/rockchip-iommu.c | 17 +++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 17 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/iommu/rockchip-iommu.c b/drivers/iommu/rockchip-iommu.c
index 0013cf196..8e4fa814d 100644
--- a/drivers/iommu/rockchip-iommu.c
+++ b/drivers/iommu/rockchip-iommu.c
@@ -420,6 +420,23 @@ static int rk_iommu_enable_stall(struct rk_iommu *iommu)
 	if (!rk_iommu_is_paging_enabled(iommu))
 		return 0;
 
+	/*
+	 * A pending page fault on an idle IOMMU prevents the hardware from
+	 * accepting CMD_ENABLE_STALL.  This can occur after a power-on when
+	 * firmware left the IOMMU with a latched fault from an unmapped access.
+	 * Clear the fault before requesting stall; doing so is safe when IDLE
+	 * is set because no transaction is actively in flight.
+	 */
+	for (i = 0; i < iommu->num_mmu; i++) {
+		u32 status = rk_iommu_read(iommu->bases[i], RK_MMU_STATUS);
+
+		if ((status & RK_MMU_STATUS_PAGE_FAULT_ACTIVE) &&
+		    (status & RK_MMU_STATUS_IDLE)) {
+			rk_iommu_base_command(iommu->bases[i], RK_MMU_CMD_ZAP_CACHE);
+			rk_iommu_base_command(iommu->bases[i], RK_MMU_CMD_PAGE_FAULT_DONE);
+		}
+	}
+
 	rk_iommu_command(iommu, RK_MMU_CMD_ENABLE_STALL);
 
 	ret = readx_poll_timeout(rk_iommu_is_stall_active, iommu, val,
-- 
